entry.content:
Protobuf itself has `SerializeToFileDescriptor(int file_descriptor)` and `SerializeToOstream(std::ostream* output)`.

`base::File` can convert to a PlatformFile, which is an `int fd` on non-Win but a `HANDLE` on Windows (which protobuf can't write to). (There's _open_osfhandle() on Windows, but it's a layer of indirection).


There's https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:components/paint_preview/common/file_utils.cc;l=15 which does:

```
bool WriteProtoToFile(const base::FilePath& file_path,
                      const PaintPreviewProto& proto) {
  // TODO(crbug.com/1046925): stream to file instead.
  std::string proto_str;
  if (!proto.SerializeToString(&proto_str))
    return false;
  return base::WriteFile(file_path, proto_str);
}
```

This creates the whole serialized data in memory instead of streaming.

There's https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:services/webnn/coreml/graph_builder.cc;l=586?q=std::fstream%20-file:third_party&ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc which does:

```
bool GraphBuilder::SerializeModel() {
  base::ElapsedTimer ml_model_write_timer;
  // This will always overwrite if there is an existing file.
  std::fstream model_file(ml_package_dir()
                              .Append(kMlPackageDataDir)
                              .Append(kMlPackageModelFileName)
                              .value(),
                          std::ios::out | std::ios::binary);
  bool result = ml_model_.SerializeToOstream(&model_file);
  UMA_HISTOGRAM_MEDIUM_TIMES("WebNN.CoreML.TimingMs.MLModelWrite",
                             ml_model_write_timer.Elapsed());
  return result;
}
```


This uses an fstream, which

1) protobuf itself discourages [1]
2) On Windows, `.value()` returns a wstring, and there's a `const std::filesystem::path::value_type*` fstream ctor [3]. But std::filesystem use is banned [2]. Then again. it only uses a typedef from there and it's a complicated way to spell `wchar_t*` [4]. So that'd probably ok. But libc++ also broke that ctor [5].




There's also https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/apps/almanac_api_client/proto_file_manager.h;l=41?q=writeprototofile&ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc which does some work to prevent partial writes of protobufs.



It'd be good to have some nice, unified way of saving protobufs.



1: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/protobuf/src/google/protobuf/io/zero_copy_stream_impl.h;l=140;drc=2a5aaed0ff3a0895c8551495c2656ed49baf742c :

```
// FileOutputStream is preferred over using an ofstream with
// OstreamOutputStream.  The latter will introduce an extra layer of buffering,
// harming performance. 
```

2: https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/main/styleguide/c++/c++-features.md#std_filesystem-banned

3: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/basic_fstream/basic_fstream

4: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/filesystem/path , look for "value_type".

5: https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/pull/85079
